          "Given the manufacturer-defined appliance type is unavailable for an appliance, when the dashboard is displayed, then the appliance remains visible and the type field shows a defined unavailable fallback instead of an empty, misleading, or incorrect type label."
        ],
        "preconditions": [
          "A test user is authenticated and has permission to view the test home.",
          "The dashboard feature for supported connected cooling appliances is enabled.",
          "The appliance data source is controllable and contains one supported connected cooling appliance assigned to the user.",
          "The app configuration defines the unavailable type fallback text as 'Type unavailable'.",
          "The appliance has no retrievable manufacturer-defined appliance type in the data source for this test."
        ],
        "testData": [
          "Appliance id: cool-unknown-type-001, display name: Pantry Cooler.",
          "Manufacturer-defined appliance type: null/not returned by data source.",
          "Expected fallback type label: Type unavailable."
        ],
        "steps": [
          {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "action": "Configure the appliance data source to return the appliance 'Pantry Cooler' without a manufacturer-defined appliance type field or with the field set to null.",
